<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
		Universal Links / Associated Domains
		────────────────────────────────────
		Each `applinks:<host>` entry tells iOS that tapping a https://<host>/...
		URL should open this app (Bundle ID: com.ecologic.app) instead of
		opening Safari or the App Store. iOS verifies each domain by fetching
		https://<host>/.well-known/apple-app-site-association at install time
		(and periodically thereafter) and matching the appID in that file
		(M9WJ473PV5.com.ecologic.app) against this entitlement.

		Required hosts:
		  • ecologic.onelink.me        → AppsFlyer OneLink shortener; the
		                                  domain that hosts the AASA file
		                                  AppsFlyer auto-generates from the
		                                  OneLink template's "iOS app" tab.
		  • ecologicc.com              → root marketing/landing host
		  • staging.ecologicc.com      → staging customer app host
		  • app.ecologicc.com          → production customer app host

		If any one of these is missing here, tapping a link on that host on a
		device with the app installed will silently fall back to the web URL
		(or to the App Store, in the OneLink case) instead of being delivered
		to the AppsFlyer Unified Deep Linking listener inside the app.
	-->
	<key>com.apple.developer.associated-domains</key>
	<array>
		<string>applinks:ecologic.onelink.me</string>
		<string>applinks:ecologicc.com</string>
		<string>applinks:staging.ecologicc.com</string>
		<string>applinks:app.ecologicc.com</string>
	</array>
	<key>aps-environment</key>
	<string>development</string>
</dict>
</plist>
